Multica Ultimate Workbench — Multi-License
===========================================

This repository is multi-licensed under three tiers. The governing principle:

  "Protocols are free. Implementation is free. Learnings stay open."

See LICENSING.md for the definitive directory-by-directory mapping and
the rationale behind each tier.

    +----------------------------------------------+---------------------------+
    | Part of repository                           | Applicable license        |
    +----------------------------------------------+---------------------------+
    | Workbench Protocols: schema contracts,       | Apache License 2.0        |
    | registry card format, evidence record,       | (LICENSE-APACHE)          |
    | sandbox run record, decision packet,         |                           |
    | runtime backend schema, ActiveMemoryPacket   |                           |
    | template, Capy card format,                  |                           |
    | HERMES_SANDBOX_RUN_RECORD contract,          |                           |
    | issue template contracts                     |                           |
    +----------------------------------------------+---------------------------+
    | Workbench Implementation: scripts,           | Apache License 2.0        |
    | dashboards, autopilots, skills, CLI tools,   | (LICENSE-APACHE)          |
    | server modules, runtime panel, serve-*.mjs,  |                           |
    | repo configs,                                |                           |
    | *.sh, *.mjs, *.js, *.css, *.html             |                           |
    +----------------------------------------------+---------------------------+
    | Workbench Learnings: friction patterns,      | CC BY-SA 4.0              |
    | lane documents, parked specs, belief epics,  | (LICENSE-CC-BY-SA)        |
    | learning sessions, schema docs,              |                           |
    | DEPARK_MANIFEST, DECISIONS.md,               |                           |
    | SYNTHESIS.md, AGENTS.md,                     |                           |
    | .learning/**, docs/** (lane docs)            |                           |
    +----------------------------------------------+---------------------------+

The three-tier model is intentional:

Tier 1 (Protocols — Apache 2.0): The interface specifications are the
interchange format. Anyone can implement them in any language, on any
platform, with or without modifications. The patent grant (§3) ensures
no contributor can later claim patent infringement against an
independent implementation of these protocols.

Tier 2 (Implementation — Apache 2.0): The reference implementation is
free to fork, adapt, and embed. Teams can use it as a starting point,
commercial users can deploy it, and derivative implementations can
share code freely. This is the same license Kubernetes, Multica, and
OpenAI Agents SDK use for the same reason.

Tier 3 (Learnings — CC BY-SA 4.0): The operational knowledge — lane
docs, friction patterns, parked specs, belief archives — is where the
thinking lives. Attribution-ShareAlike means anyone can use it
commercially, but improvements and derivatives must remain under the
same license. This prevents a company from taking Workbench patterns,
improving them privately, and closing the improvements. The upstream
stays open, and every derivative keeps the chain of attribution back
to this repository.

This multi-licensing model makes Workbench THE UPSTREAM: the protocols
are free to adopt, the implementation is free to fork, and the learnings
cannot be closed.

